article.headline: Anderson's double-double lifts BYU over TCU
article.linkText: Anderson's double-double lifts BYU over TCU
article.story:
FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Ambrosia Anderson scored 24 points, 
including six 3-pointers, and had a team-high 10 rebounds to help 
lead No. 20 Brigham Young to a 67-64 win over TCU on Wednesday 
night.

Dani Kubik added 16 points on 5-of-7 shooting, and Mallary
Gillespie had 12 points for BYU (16-1, 6-0 Mountain West), which
rallied from a 35-28 halftime deficit.

TCU trailed by eight points with 1½ minutes left in the game,
but pulled to within three on a jumper by Adrianne Ross with 20
seconds remaining. Ashley Davis missed a 3-pointer with 1 second
left that would have tied the game.

Lorie Butler-Rayford scored 16 points to lead TCU (10-7, 4-2).
Natasha Lacy added 11 points and a team-high 12 rebounds.
